<subSubSection id="C34B6565FFF3FFF5FF284C742E44FE39" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEE36EEFFF3FFF5FF284C742E44FE39" blockId="9.[151,1437,351,486]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFF3FFF5FF284C742B68FEA6" bold="true" box="[151,287,351,377]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Comments.</emphasis>
The species was described according to 
<specimenCount id="9D57FD67FFF3FFF5FD554C4B2905FEA6" box="[746,882,351,378]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
collected in 
<location id="8E8E6035FFF3FFF5FBBC4C742EDCFEA6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F887F8FFF3FFF5FF284DBC2E44FE39:8E8E6035FFF3FFF5FBBC4C742EDCFEA6" box="[1027,1195,351,377]" municipality="western Transcaucasia. However" name="Shakalya Cave" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Shakalya Cave</location>
in 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B8AAC94FFF3FFF5FB704C4B2B32FE41" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">western Transcaucasia. However</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<typeStatus id="54EA884CFFF3FFF5FEEF4CAF2BF7FE41" box="[336,384,388,414]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">type</typeStatus>
material is not available (
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FD1E4CA8294EFE42" box="[673,825,387,413]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">K. Mikhailov</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FCFB4CAF29D1FE41" box="[836,934,388,414]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Moscow</collectorName>
, and 
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FC604CAF2E03FE42" box="[991,1140,387,414]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">E. Perkovsky</collectorName>
, 
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FBC04CA82EC1FE42" box="[1151,1206,387,413]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Kiev</collectorName>
, in litt.). 
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FAA54CA82F31FE42" box="[1306,1350,387,413]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">The</collectorName>
male is unknown. 
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FEB24C832B69FE1D" box="[269,286,424,450]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">It</collectorName>
is impossible to decide on the generic and species identity. 
<collectorName id="26A45338FFF3FFF5FC0B4C8C29A7FE1E" box="[948,976,423,449]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">At</collectorName>
present, we must consider this species as 
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFF3FFF5FF284CE72B1EFE3A" box="[151,361,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">species inquirenda</emphasis>
and the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D6DFFF3FFF5FDB34CE0289AFE3A" authorityName="Pichka" authorityYear="1965" box="[524,749,459,485]" class="Arachnida" family="Hahniidae" genus="Iberina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ljovuschkini">
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFF3FFF5FDB34CE0289AFE3A" box="[524,749,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Iberina ljovuschkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is declared a 
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFF3FFF5FC384CE72E5BFE3A" box="[903,1068,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">nomen dubium</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
